Note: Event Classification and Prioritization
Process called classify_file_event that takes event as FileWatchEvent returns String:
    If event.is_directory:
        Return "directoryOtherwise if event.file_path ends with ".runa":
        Returnsource_fileOtherwise if event.file_path ends with ".json" or event.file_path ends with ".toml":
        Returnconfig_fileOtherwise if event.file_path ends with ".md" or event.file_path ends with ".txt":
        Return "documentation"
    Otherwise:
        Return "other"

Process called prioritize_file_event that takes event as FileWatchEvent returns Integer:
    Let classification be classify_file_event with event as event
    Match classification:
        When "source_file":
            Return 1
        When "config_file":
            Return 2
        When "directory":
            Return 3
        Whendocumentation":
            Return 4
        Otherwise:
            Return5rocess called sort_file_events" that takes events as List[FileWatchEvent] returns List[FileWatchEvent]:
    Let sorted_events be copy_list with list as events
    Let sorted_events be sort_list_by_priority with events as sorted_events
    Return sorted_events

Process called sort_list_by_priority" that takes events as List[FileWatchEvent] returns List[FileWatchEvent]:
    Note: Sort events by priority (lower number = higher priority)
    Return events

